'''''Kadal''''' (''''The Sea'''') is a 2013 [[Indian cinema|Indian]] [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] drama film<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/4497 |title="Kadal is not a romantic film" <U+2013> Mani Ratnam |author=Subhash K. Jha|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=2 February 2012}}</ref> directed and co-produced by [[Mani Ratnam]].<ref name=bdgt/> The film features debutantes [[Gautham Karthik]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/meet-mani-ratnams-hero/20121206.htm |title=Meet Mani Ratnam's hero, Gautham Karthik |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref> son of actor [[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]], and [[Thulasi Nair]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/first-look-mani-ratnams-heroine-in-kadal/20121210.htm |title=First Look: Mani Ratnam's heroine in Kadal |publisher=Rediff |accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref> daughter of [[Radha (actress)|Radha]], in the lead roles. The film marks [[comeback]] of actor [[Arvind Swamy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=I DIDN'T WATCH ANY MOVIE FOR 5 TO 6 YEARS, HAVE TO CATCH-UP <U+2013> ARVIND SWAMY|url=http://behindwoods.com/new-videos/tamil-actors/i-didnt-watch-any-movie-for-5-to-6-years-have-to-catch-up---arvind-swamy/arvind-swamy-interview.html|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref> The music and background score for the film is done by [[A. R. Rahman]]. The film revolves around life of Christian fishermen who instill the fact that how faith can sometimes lead to the triumph of humanity.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Music/Never-believed-world-would-end-AR-Rahman/Article1-979347.aspx| title=Never believed world would end: AR Rahman|author=Nirmika Singh|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|date= 22 December 2012 |accessdate=22 December 2012}}</ref> The film is titled ''Kadali'', as the dubbed [[Telugu language|Telugu]] version.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/sep-12-03/kadal-kadali-18-09-12.html |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal becomes Kadali |publisher=Behindwoods |date=18 September 2012 |accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Reddy|first=Lohit|title=''Kadal'' to be dubbed in Telugu as ''Kadali''|url=http://www.realbollywood.com/2012/09/kadal-dubbed-telugu-kadali.html|publisher=RealBollywood.com|accessdate=4 November 2012}}</ref> The film was released worldwide on 1 February 2013 in both the versions.<ref name=release1/> The film received mixed reviews from critics and lukewarm response from audience. From the main film aspects, the cinematography, music and background score were critically applauded.

==Plot==
Berchmans ([[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]]), a brilliant but unruly student, is thrown out of his seminary for committing the sin of the flesh after being caught red-handed by fellow student Sam Fernando ([[Arvind Swamy|Arvind Swami]]). Blaming the good-hearted Sam for his ouster, Berchmans vows revenge and challenges to prove that evil does reign supreme in this world. Sam finishes his education and training and arrives at a village as the new Father of the local church. A local boy named Thomas of this village who is the illegitimate son of a local fisherman ([[Ponvannan]]) has grown up in a rough neighbourhood, following the death of his mother and thus being forced to fend for himself.

Father Sam takes the run down church and the sceptic villagers in his stride and soon starts bringing about changes. Through a series of incidents, he also manages to get the unruly Thomas under his control and gets him to learn the tricks of the fishing trade from the villagers. The film fast forwards a few years when Thomas is now all grown up ([[Gautham Karthik]]) and is very close to Father Sam who is now a well respected person in the village.

Thomas comes across Bea (short for Beatrice) ([[Thulasi Nair]]) when she's running away from her convent school group who had gotten her admitted to hospital. They keep running into each other a few times and Thomas comes to like her presence.

Meanwhile, as Father Sam is meditating on the remote beach, he hears a few gunshots on the sands. On investigation, he finds an unconscious Berchmans in the waters. On seeing that the shooters are still lurking around trying to finish their job of killing Berchmans, he pulls him to safety into an abandoned ship, and takes care of his bullet injuries with the help of a local village woman as well as a woman from a distant village that Berchmans asks him to get. A few villagers including Ponvannan who see Father Sam running around in the dark with the 2 women get suspicious and accuse the three of sleeping together. They call the Bishop, upon whose interrogation, the woman that Berchmans had invited admits to the sin, and Father Sam gets unfairly implicated. One of the villagers also gets killed in the ensuing m<U+00EA>l<U+00E9>e and Father Sam gets sentenced to 4 years rigorous imprisonment.

Berchmans visits Father Sam in prison and admits he got the woman to implicate him falsely, to prove that evil will always triumph. When Father Sam returns from prison, he discovers Thomas has fallen in cahoots with the evil Berchmans in his smuggling trade and has committed many sins in his desire to make the village people bow before him. Thomas and Bea have also fallen in love with each other and come to seek Father Sam's blessings. Thomas subsequently gets to know that Bea is none other than the estranged daughter of Berchmans, who does not want to have to do anything with her.

Thomas takes Bea to Berchmans' house to trigger some long-lost memories when she recalls all the previous horrific incidents of her father Berchmans, including the one of killing her mother. Berchmans gets angry with all this and abducts both Father Sam and Bea in his boat and goes out to sea with an intent to kill them both. However even after a few feeble attempts, the self-professed son of Satan who disavows all family attachment, is unable to get himself to kill his daughter. Thomas comes chasing them and after a long drawn fight amongst the three, Thomas and Father Sam together manage to subdue the evil Bergmans.

The movie ends on a note that good finally triumphs over evil, whether it be Father Sam and Thomas' triumph over Berchmans, Thomas' own suppressing of his bad inclination and re-joining forces with Father Sam, or Berchmans' good nature coming out in his inability to kill his daughter.

==Cast==
*[[Gautham Karthik]] as Thomas
*[[Thulasi Nair]] as Beatrice/Bea
*[[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]] as Berchmans
*[[Arvind Swamy]] as Father Sam Fernando
*[[Ponvannan]] as Chetty
*[[Lakshmi Manchu]] as Celina
*[[Kalairani]] as Mother Superior

==Production==

===Development===
During a press meet in December 2009, actor [[Karthik (actor)|Karthik]] revealed that his son, [[Gautham Karthik]] would make his debut in [[Mani Ratnam]]'s next venture post completion of Ratnam's bilingual films ''[[Raavan]]'' and ''[[Raavanan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/52468.html |title=Mani Ratnam to launch Karthik's son! <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> In July 2010, reports emerged that the film was titled as ''Pookkadai''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58490.html |title=Mani's next 'Pookkadai'? <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> Mani Ratnam stopped pre-production work on the film in late 2010 and moved on to plan a big-budget historical project titled ''Ponniyin Selvan'', but months later was forced to shelve it due to financial issues. Later, owing to the speculated title of the former project, the team was unable to name the film ''Pookkadai'' as an aspiring director had already registered the name in 2007. Finally the working project was renamed as ''Kadal'' in February 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/76897.html |title=It's not 'Pookadai' for Mani! <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref>
When Mani Ratnam  had finished ''[[Raavanan]]'' (2010), [[Jeyamohan]] started writing a 200-page novel for ''Kadal'', which was later transformed by Mani Ratnam into a screenplay.<ref name=jeyhindu>{{cite news|title=Sea of imagination|url=http://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/metroplus/sea-of-imagination/article4365144.ece|accessdate=31 January 2013|newspaper=The Hindu|date=31 January 2013}}</ref> Jeyamohan was signed to be a part of the script-writing team for the film in August 2011, while [[Rajiv Menon]] was also confirmed as cinematographer for the film, reuniting with Mani Ratnam after the successes of ''[[Bombay (film)|Bombay]]'' and ''[[Guru (2007 film)|Guru]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/aug-11-03/mani-rathnam-rajiv-menon-19-08-11.html |title=More on Mani Ratnam's Next <U+2013> Mani Ratnam <U+2013> Rajiv Menon <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=19 August 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-04/news-interviews/29850163_1_mani-ratnam-mani-sir-love-story |title=A love story for Mani? |work=The Times of India |date= 4 August 2011|accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> As the film portrays Christianity, Rajiv Menon explored the way artistes capture biblical themes. For this he and Ratnam went through [[Simon Schama]]'s documentary called [[Simon Schama's Power of Art|Power of Art]] on [[Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio|Caravaggio]]. For the outdoor shootings they stuck to the contemporary way. Mani Ratnam's reconnaissance for the film, the process of designing the look was done when his assistants brought back hundreds of pictures after jaunting through the entire coastline of the state [[Tamil Nadu]], including [[Rameswaram]].<ref name=rmnn/>

===Casting===
Akshara Haasan, daughter of actor [[Kamal Haasan]] and actress [[Sarika]] was heavily linked to play the female lead role in August 2011 but was not signed.<ref>{{cite web|author=31 August 2011 By Anupama Subramanian DC chennai |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/node/53409 |title=Akshara Haasan in Mani Ratnam's film? |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=31 August 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> In December 2011, reports emerged that Hindi film actress [[Sonam Kapoor]] was signed on to play the role after being convinced by her father but the news was untrue.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-13/news-interviews/30511098_1_sonam-kapoor-hindi-film-mani-ratnam |title=Sonam Kapoor in Mani Ratnam's next film |work=The Times of India |date= 13 December 2011|accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> Jhanvi, daughter of producer [[Boney Kapoor]] and actress [[Sridevi]], was also considered to play the role.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/20661/kollywood/Mani-Ratnam-s-next-movie-got-Sri-Devi-s-daughter-News-Details |title=Mani Ratnam's next movie with Sri Devi's daughter |publisher=Super Good Movies |date=28 June 2011}}</ref> Finally in January 2012, it was revealed that [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]] was confirmed to portray the lead female role, making film ''Kadal'' her most high-profile project till date.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-01-11/news-interviews/30615637_1_mani-ratnam-samantha-pookadai |title=Samantha bags lead in Pookadai |work=The Times of India |date= 11 January 2012|accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> After production had begun, Samantha was forced to opt out of the film in June 2012 due to her [[Polymorphous light eruption|PMLE]] ailments.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3500935.ece | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | first=K. R. | last=Manigandan | title=Shot Cuts: Samantha out of <U+2018>Kadal' | date=7 June 2012}}</ref> The ace director replaced the lead female by signing Thulasi Nair, the second daughter of actress [[Radha (actress)|Radha]]. Though Thulasi was auditioned for the role during the casting process, she was not selected as Ratnam opined that she was too young for the role. Post Samantha's exit, she was roped in.<ref name=tag.three>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-29/news-interviews/34149144_1_mani-ratnam-gautham-karthik-karthika |title=If not for Mani Ratnam, I wouldn<U+2019>t be in films: Thulasi |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=29 September 2012 |accessdate=24 November 2012}}</ref><ref name="articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-04/news-interviews/30112588_1_mani-ratnam-karthika-ponniyin-selvan |title=Mani to launch Karthika's sister? |work=The Times of India |date= 4 September 2011|accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref><ref name="articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/82786.html |title=Mani Ratnam picks Thulasi |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=9 June 2012 |accessdate=9 June 2012}}</ref> The child actress in Mani Ratnam's 2002 film ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'', [[P. S. Keerthana|Keerthana]] was approached for a role but she chose to join the film's team as an assistant director, instead.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-01/news-interviews/30345486_1_mani-ratnam-ponniyin-selvan-gautham |title=Mani's search continues... |work=The Times of India |date= 1 November 2011|accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Y. Sunita Chowdhary |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2744546.ece |title=Arts / Cinema : 'You guys have forgotten me' |work=The Hindu |date=24 December 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-24 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref>

In November 2011, actor [[Arjun Sarja|Arjun]] was signed to play a pivotal role in the film, denying reports that he would play the villain,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-11-08/news-interviews/30378321_1_mani-ratnam-bollywood-film-pivotal-character |title=Arjun Sarja in Mani's next |work=The Times of India |date=8 November 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/article325060.ece | title=I'm not the villain in 'Kadal': Arjun | work=[[The New Indian Express]] | date=27 February 2012 | accessdate=13 March 2013 | author=Sruthi Kannath}}</ref> though this was later revealed to be misdirection.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/from-kadal-to-kaadhal/article4446325.ece | title=From Kadal to Kaadhal | work=The Hindu | date=23 February 2013 | accessdate=13 March 2013 | author=Malathi Rangarajan}}</ref> [[Lakshmi Manchu]] would be playing a village belle in a negative shade,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/telugu/news-interviews/Im-not-doing-an-item-song-Lakshmi-Manchu/articleshow/17266651.cms |title=I<U+2019>m not doing an item song: Lakshmi Manchu |date=18 November 2011 |accessdate=2012-11-18}}</ref> making her debut in Tamil films.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-12-17/news-interviews/30528184_1_lakshmi-manchu-tamil-cinema-kollywood |title=Lakshmi Manchu in Mani Ratnam's Pookadai |work=The Times of India |date=17 December 2011 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> Actors [[Pasupathy]] and [[Lal (actor)|Lal]] were opted for supporting roles in the film,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/75930.html |title=Pasupathi, Lal in Mani's next? <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> but Lal dropped the film due to his commitments to Malayalam film ''[[Ozhimuri]]''.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-05/news-and-interviews/31574267_1_mani-ratnam-lal-actor | work=The Times of India | title=Lal's commitment forces him to say no to Mani Ratnam | date=5 May 2012}}</ref> [[Arvind Swamy]] who returned to films post twelve years, was signed to play a full fledged role.<ref>{{cite web|author=31 January 2012 By Anupama Subramanian DC chennai |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/showbiz/kollywood/arvind-swamy-joins-mani-ratnam%E2%80%99s-film-812 |title=Arvind Swamy joins Mani Ratnam's film |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=31 January 2012 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> [[Thambi Ramiah]] was also confirmed to be a part of the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-12-01/mani-rathnam-gautham-01-02-12.html |title=Mani Ratnam Picks The National Award Winner? <U+2013> Mani Ratnam <U+2013> Gautham <U+2013> Thambi Ramaiah <U+2013> Tamil Movie News |publisher=Behindwoods.com |date=1 February 2012 |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> Child artiste Saran, earlier seen in films such as ''[[Mudhal Idam]]'' and ''Mye'', would be seen playing Gautham Karthik's childhood role.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article3363978.ece |title=Itsy-Bitsy |work=The Hindu |date=28 April 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-30 |location=Chennai, India |first=Nikhil |last=Raghavan}}</ref> Theater artiste Devi would be essaying the role actor Gautham's mother.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/may-12-05/mani-ratnam-samantha-29-05-12.html |title=Mani Ratnam makes an interesting addition |publisher=Behindwoods |date=29 May 2012 |accessdate=26 October 2012}}</ref> Baby Rakshana would be playing the role of childhood Thulasi. Mani Ratnam roped in [[Nayantara]] for a special role in the film which was confirmed in early July 2012.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-02/news-interviews/32507700_1_nayanthara-mani-ratnam-prabhu-deva |title=Nayanthara's special role in Kadal |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=2 July 2012 |accessdate=14 July 2012}}</ref> However, the actress opted out claiming unavailability of dates and meager scope of her character in the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-13/news-interviews/32214227_1_nayantara-mani-ratnam-upcoming-flick |title=Nayantara in Mani Ratnam's Kadal? |work=The Times of India |date=13 June 2012 |accessdate=14 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinebuzzz.com/articles/727/Nayanthara-walks-out-from-Kadal- |title=Nayanthara walks out from Kadal  |publisher=Cinebuzz |date=29 August 2012 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref> Malayalam comedian Baiju was selected to play a supporting role.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/84678.html |title=Malayalam comedian as character artist in Kadal? |publisher=Indiaglitz |date=11 August 2012}}</ref>

===Filming===
{{Quote box|width=40%|align=right|quote= <U+201C>One reason is the film's ability to take a battering<U+2014>the cameras are so solid and the horizon blows out in digital camerawork, it becomes white and the sea and the sky become one.<U+201D>|source=<U+2014>[[Rajiv Menon]] on the use of [[35 mm film]] camera for ''Kadal'' making it one of the last Tamil films to use [[film stock]].<ref>{{cite web|title=In Focus <U+2013> Angling partners|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/NLxlQGeAKoxvcVCnHZSKlL/In-Focus--Angling-partners.html|author=Nandini Ramnath (First Published: January 18, 2013 <U+2013> 1806 HRS IST)|work=LiveMint|accessdate=10 March 2013}}</ref>}}

Keeping principal photography under wraps, the director made the leading duo to undertake a 20-day acting workshop that was conducted by his crew.<ref name=tag.three/> Later, a two-month acting workshop under the mentorship of actress Kalairani was also attended by them.<ref name=tagb>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/age-cant-be-a-barrier-for-acting-thulasi-nair/317957-71-180.html|title=Kadal: Age can't be a barrier for acting, says 16-year-old Thulasi Nair|accessdate=27 January 2013|publisher''IBN Live''=The Hindu|date=27 January 2013}}</ref> The shooting of the film started on 1 March 2012 at [[Manapad]], a sea village in [[Thoothukudi]] district. Scenes involving Arvind Swamy and Lakshmi Manchu were shot first.<ref>{{cite web|author=Shankar |url=http://tamil.oneindia.in/movies/specials/2012/03/maniratnam-s-kadal-shooting-begins-aid0136.html |title=Maniratnam's Kadal shooting begins at Manapad &#124; <U+0BAE><U+0BA3><U+0BAA><U+0BCD><U+0BAA><U+0BBE><U+0B9F><U+0BC1> <U+0B95><U+0BBF><U+0BB0><U+0BBE><U+0BAE><U+0BA4><U+0BCD><U+0BA4><U+0BBF><U+0BB2><U+0BCD> <U+0BA4><U+0BCA><U+0B9F><U+0B99><U+0BCD><U+0B95><U+0BBF><U+0BAF><U+0BA4><U+0BC1> <U+0BAE><U+0BA3><U+0BBF><U+0BB0><U+0BA4><U+0BCD><U+0BA9><U+0BA4><U+0BCD><U+0BA4><U+0BBF><U+0BA9><U+0BCD> <U+0B95><U+0B9F><U+0BB2><U+0BCD>! <U+2013> Oneindia Tamil |publisher=Tamil.oneindia.in |accessdate=2012-03-24}}</ref> In March 2012, in a schedule of five days, certain scenes were shot at [[Kottayam]], [[Muhamma]], backwaters and forts of [[Kochi]] in Kerala. The filming continued in [[Kerala]] throughout April 2012.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.supergoodmovies.com/42749/kollywood/mani-ratnam-s-kadal-location-stills-news-details |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal location stills | publisher= SuperGoodMovies | date= 8 April 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref><ref name=tag.two>{{cite web| url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2012/maniratnam-keep-kadal-actors-look-under-wrap-090412.html |title=Mani Ratnam keeps Kadal actors' look under wrap | publisher= OneIndia | date= 9 April 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref> A scene featuring the lead actors was shot at a church, created as a set in [[Tuticorin]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-16/news-interviews/31349579_1_church-love-story-karthik |title=Mani Ratnam's church in Kadal | work= [[The Times of India]] | date= 16 April 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-21}}</ref> Scenes were also canned in longest Indian lake [[Vembanad]], [[Alappuzha]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/84586.html |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal <U+2013> Vembanad Kayal bound | publisher= Indiaglitz | date= 9 August 2012 |accessdate=2012-08-10}}</ref> In the scenic interiors of [[Andaman & Nicobar Islands]], twenty days filming schedule was completed by end of July 2012.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2012/mani-ratnam-kadal-andaman-097110.html |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal unit off to Andaman | author= Ramchander|publisher= OneIndia Entertainment | date= 4 July 2012 |accessdate= 26 October 2012}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Times of India]]'' in October 2012, [[Suhasini Mani Ratnam]] revealed that filming was in its final stages.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/bollywood/news/a410229/mani-ratnam-has-no-plans-for-rebecca-remake-with-aishwarya-rai.html |title=Mani Ratnam 'has no plans for Rebecca remake with Aishwarya Rai' | author= Priya Joshi|work= Digital Spy | date= 4 October 2012 |accessdate= 26 October 2012}}</ref> On 31 October 2012, the crew shot the climax of the film in coastal suburbs of [[Chennai]] under the weather contrived by [[Cyclone Nilam]].<ref name=tag.one>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Cyclone-Nilam-couldnt-stop-Mani-Ratnam/articleshow/17059995.cms |title=Cyclone Nilam couldn't stop Mani Ratnam |work= [[The Times of India]] | date= 2 November 2012 |accessdate= 2 November 2012}}</ref> On 5 November 2012, the shooting of the film was completed except for a song to be canned in [[Alappuzha]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.kollyinsider.com/2012/11/mani-ratnam-completes-kadal-shoot.html |title=Mani Ratnam completes 'Kadal' shoot |work= Kolly Insider | date= 5 November 2012 |accessdate= 8 November 2012}}</ref> This song schedule and patchwork for the film kicked off on 13 January 2013.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Gautham-and-Thulasi-in-Alleppey/articleshow/17994755.cms |title=Gautham and Thulasi in Alleppey! |work= [[The Times of India]] | date= 12 January 2013 |accessdate= 14 January 2013}}</ref> By second last week of the same month the patch work and re-recording of the background score was completed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Prefectionists Rahman, Ratnam re-record 'Kadal' music|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tamil-movie-kadal-will-have-actors-gautham-karthik-and-thulasi-nair-in-the-lead/317300-71-180.html|publisher=IBN Live|date=23 January 2013|accessdate=26 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/90109.html|title=Kadal dubbing almost done, getting ready for final edits|publisher=Indiaglitz|accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref> Post release of theatrical trailer, it was revealed that the filming of ten second osculating scene between lead actors took four hours to complete after several re-takes. The director had devoided the technicians and crew from the location to ease the situation for the actors.<ref name=contrvs>{{cite web|title=When a 10 second long kiss took 4 hours, for Kadal|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/when-a-10-second-long-kiss-took-4-hours-for-kadal-kadal-mani-ratnam-20-01-13.html|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Picture: Gautham Karthik-Thulasi Nair's kiss in Kadal draws attention|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2013/gautham-karthik-thulasi-nair-kiss-kadal-102807.html|publisher=OneIndia|accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref> Post filming completions, the cinematographer stated that the film was set in a hard landscape. For initial portions of the film the crew created the barren look by emphasising sand colours and muffling vibrancy of costumes. Apparently, this was achieved to create an hostile environment in which the lead male character grows.<ref name=rmnn>{{cite news|last=Kamath|first=Sudhish|title=Look what's brewing|url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/look-whats-brewing/article4348055.ece|accessdate=26 January 2013|newspaper=The Hindu|date=26 January 2013}}</ref> Writer [[Jeyamohan]] told ''[[The Hindu]]'', that the script was "deeply philosophical and spiritual", "but it has been narrated in an entertaining way, complete with songs and captivating frames. It is a grand saga..", he added.<ref name=jeyhindu />

==Marketing==
In February 2012, after the official announcement of the project with title, several forged posters were released over the internet citing wrong credits and the film plot.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://middaytimes.com/mani-ratnams-kadal-first-look-posters/ |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal First look Posters|date= 16 February 2012 |accessdate=16 November 2012}}</ref> On 19 November 2012 the film's official page was launched on social networking website Facebook.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/nov-12-03/mani-ratnam-kadal-20-11-12.html |title=Mani Ratnam's Kadal's new launch|date= 20 November 2012 |accessdate=24 November 2012}}</ref> After two days the poster of the male lead concealing his visage was released through the same. In order to guard the facial identities of the debutantes,<ref name=tag.two/> Mani Ratnam requested their respective parents to not let Thulasi or Gautham Karthik be snapped by anyone. Additionally they had to refrain from public appearances. The actress refused to appear at an interview for the same reason.<ref name=tag.three/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/cine-buzz/20125801025849/Mani-Ratnams-condition-to-Radha-and-Karthik.col |title=Mani Ratnam's condition to Radha and Karthik|publisher=Chennai Online|date= 1 October 2012 |accessdate=24 November 2012}}</ref> First countenances of the lead actors were released through special posters on the film's page, Gautham Karthik's look being unveiled on 4 December 2012 and Thulasi on 10 December 2012.<ref name=tag.four>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/telugu/news-interviews/First-look-of-Thulasi-in-Mani-Ratnams-Kadal/articleshow/17567932.cms|title=First look of Thulasi in Mani Ratnam's Kadal |author= Sashidhar AS|work= [[The Times of India]]| accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref> The main theatrical trailer was released on 11 January 2013 through [[Madras Talkies]]' YouTube channel. The trailer was also attached to the theatre prints of film [[Alex Pandian]] that released on the same day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kadal-trailer-mani-ratnam-returns-with-a-high-voltage-romantic-drama/315317-71-183.html|title='Kadal' trailer: Mani Ratnam returns with a high voltage romantic drama TA |publisher= IBN Live| accessdate=13 January 2013}}</ref> In a frenzy, the trailer crossed 1 million views within a day of its release on ''YouTube''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-16/news-interviews/36372981_1_mani-ratnam-arvind-swami-son-of-yesteryear-actor|title='Kadal' trailer creates buzz!|work= [[The Times of India]]| date=16 January 2013|accessdate=20 January 2013}}</ref>

==Music==
{{Main|Kadal (soundtrack)}}
Director [[Mani Ratnam]]'s usual associate music composer, [[A. R. Rahman]] composed the songs as well as the background score for the film. The lyrics of three songs were penned by [[Vairamuthu]], other three by his son [[Madhan Karky]] and remaining one by rapper Aaryan Dinesh Kanagaratnam, making the album feature seven tracks in the [[Kadal (soundtrack)|soundtrack album]]. The album was scheduled to release on 17 December 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Kadal-audio-on-Dec-17/articleshow/17518408.cms |title='Kadal' audio on Dec 17 |work= [[The Times of India]]|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref> but due to tremendous pre-booking orders, the audio label advanced the release by two days.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Kadal-audio-creates-history/articleshow/17623303.cms|title='Kadal' audio creates history!|work= [[The Times of India]]|date= 15 December 2012 |accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> The original (Tamil) version of the album was released on 15 December 2012 by the record label [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony Music]]. It opened up with extremely positive reviews, topping the Indian music charts, especially [[ITunes|iTunes India]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Elay-keechan-top-itunes-chart/articleshow/17568077.cms|title='Elay keechan' top itunes chart|author=Shiva Prasad|work= [[The Times of India]] |date= 11 December 2012 |accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref> The [[Telugu language|Telugu]] version of the soundtrack album was released direct to stores on 26 December 2012 and was also launched in a grand event at H.I.C.C. [[Novotel]], [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] on 10 January 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Mani-Ratnam-has-grand-Kadal-Telugu-audio-launch/articleshow/17965979.cms|title=Mani Ratnam has grand Kadal Telugu audio launch|author=Lata Srinivasan|work= [[The Times of India]] |date=10 January 2013|accessdate=10 January 2013}}</ref>

==Release==
;Domestic
[[Gemini Film Circuit]] bought the theatrical rights of the film for {{INR}} 250&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/apr-12-01/gemini-films-kadal-04-04-12.html |title=Gemini films procures Mani Ratnam's Kadal |publisher= Behindwoods |date= 4 April 2012 |accessdate=2012-04-05}}</ref> In January 2013, [[Vijay TV]] acquired the satellite telecast rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2013/vijay-tv-acquires-kadal-satellite-rights-102659.html |title=Vijay TV acquires Kadal satellite rights |publisher=OneIndia Entertainment|author=Ramchander |accessdate=17 January 2013}}</ref> In mid-January 2013, ''Kadal'' was censored with a [[Central Board of Film Certification#Current certificates|U certificate]] from the [[Indian Censor Board]] after five minor cuts.<ref name=runtime/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-01-19/news-interviews/36431167_1_u-certificate-gautham-karthik-and-thulasi-mani-ratnam-s-madras-talkies |title=Kadal censored with 'U' certificate |work= [[The Times of India]] |date=19 January 2013 |accessdate=20 January 2013}}</ref> The advanced booking opened two days prior to the release. However, the distributors in [[Tamil Nadu]] faced arduousness for screen occupancies due to controversial release status of film ''[[Vishwaroopam]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kadal-advance-booking-starts-two-days-before-the-release/369480-71-180.html |title=Kadal: Advance booking starts two days before the release|publisher= Indiaglitz |date=29 January 2013 |accessdate=29 January 2013}}</ref>

;Overseas
ATMUS Entertainment bagged the distribution rights of the film in USA. The original (Tamil) version was release in 54 screens and dubbed (Telugu) version in 20 screens. The film was premiered in most of the locations of the same country a day prior to the actual release.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/90457.html |title=Kadal/Kadali geared up for big USA release!|publisher=Indiaglitz|date=29 January 2013 |accessdate=29 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=oversrel>{{cite web |url=http://www.kollybuzz.com/home/news/kadal-all-set-for-a-huge-release-in-usa/ |title=Kadal <U+2013> All set for a Huge release in USA|publisher=Kollybuzz|author=vbzu|date=29 January 2013 |accessdate=29 January 2013}}</ref>

