Kadal received mixed reviews from critics. At ''[[DNA India]]'', critic Mahalakshmi Prabhakaran quoted, "A poignant film", further adding, "The only drawback of the movie might be the fact that it drags towards the end. Else, go and watch Kadal. It is a beautifully made film.".<ref name=dna>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/review_review-kadal-tamil_1795430|title=Review: Kadal (Tamil)|publisher=DNA India|author=Mahalakshmi Prabhakaran|location = [[Bengaluru]]|date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> On the contrary, ''Indiaglitz'' stated, "Too obvious to be an entertainer, too downplayed to be a classic" and added (that the film was) "overly commercial and no real Mani Ratnam effect".<ref name=ig>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/16291.html|title=Kadal Movie Review |publisher=Indiaglitz|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kadal-review-too-obvious-to-be-an-entertainer-too-downplayed-to-be-a-classic/370201-71-178.html |title='Kadal' Review: |publisher=IBNLive|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref> However, the Telugu version was reviewed contrary by the same source stating, "With a beautiful story and an imaginative screenplay, Kadali is a breathtaking film topped with fine performances which convey a range of emotions; the film weaves a number of immensely watchable scenes."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/telugu/review/17131.html|title=Kadali Movie Review |publisher=Indiaglitz|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> Radhika Rajamani of ''[[Rediff]]'' quoted, "Kadal has all the elements of a regular entertainer but has nothing new in terms of a story" thereby summarising, "Kadal has nothing new to offer".<ref name=rdf>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/south-review-kadal-has-nothing-new-to-offer/20130201.htm |title=Review: Kadal has nothing new to offer |publisher=[[Rediff]]|author=Radhika Rajamani|location=Hyderabad|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref> Shekhar of ''OneIndia'' said, "Kadali is a beautiful romance drama with some commercial ingredients like action and punch dialogues."<ref name=oi>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/telugu/reviews/2013/kadali-movie-review-103117.html|title=Kadali <U+2013> Movie Review |publisher=[[Oneindia.in|One India Entertainment]]|author=Shekhar|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref> T.S. Sudhir at ''Firstpost'' stated, "Mani Ratnam's Kadal leaves viewers at sea".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/review-mani-ratnams-kadal-leaves-viewers-at-sea-610195.html|title=Review: Kadal|publisher=Firstpost|author=T.S. Sudhir|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref> Nandini Ramnath at ''Livemint'' noted, "Kadal is not a perfect storm, but it's far from a sinking proposition. It floats comfortably midstream, coasting along on the strength of attractive actors and visuals." However she added more by stating, "A predictable story layered with strong performances"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/TU2oPhpl38YS5Jta808h7O/Film-Review--Kadal.html?ref=dd |author=Nandini Ramnath|title=Film Review : Kadal |publisher=Livemint|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=1 February 2013}}</ref> At ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'', Khalid Mohamed wrote, "Well, Mani still matters".<ref name=dc>{{cite web |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/130202/entertainment-movie-reviews/article/kadal-review-well-mani-still-matters |author=Khalid Mohamed|title='Kadal' review |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> Kanchana Devi at ''Truthdive'' pointed out, "Kadal has a wonderful script. The slow-paced narration is the drawback, which tests the patience of the viewers. But it could be watched once for the attempt of Mani Ratnam."<ref name=td>{{cite web |url=http://truthdive.com/2013/02/01/kadal-kadali-review.html |author=Kanchana Devi|title=Kadal (Kadali) <U+2013> Review |publisher=Truthdive|date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> M. Suganth of ''[[The Times of India]]'' noted, "Kadal's flaws are even more glaring. It is a failure for Mani Ratnam the storyteller, saved only to a certain extent by his visual flair."<ref name=toi>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Kadal/movie-review/18295736.cms |author=M. Suganth|title=Kadal (Review) |work=[[The Times of India]]|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> The critical review board at ''Behindwoods'' quoted, "Technically brilliant, but wanting in Mani Ratnam's magic".<ref name=bw>{{cite web |url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/kadal/kadal-movie-review.html |author=M. Suganth|title=KADAL MOVIE REVIEW |publisher=Behindwoods|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref>''Sify'' reviewed, "Straight off the bat, Mani Ratnam's Kadal is nowhere in the league of his earlier films." However, applauded other aspects stating, "Rajiv Menon's striking camerawork, AR Rahman's music is one of the major plus of the film".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=15019156&ctid=5&cid=2429 |title=KADAL REVIEW |publisher=Sify|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref>''[[Sahara India Pariwar|Sahara Samay]]'' attributed the film title stating, "Confusion lasts like a sea. At the end the, movies seems like a tussle between fishing net and church." However, they added, "The music by A.R. Rahman is good and cinematography is at its best."<ref name=ss>{{cite web |url=http://english.samaylive.com/entertainment-news/676523086/kadal-review-confusion-lasts-like-a-sea.html |title=Kadal review |publisher=Sahara Samay|date=1 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> Sangeetha Devi Dundoo of ''[[The Hindu]]'' who reviewed the Telugu version said, "Kadali is a visual and musical treat but content wise, the sailing isn<U+2019>t smooth."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/kadali-turbulent-flow/article4369096.ece |title=Kadali: Turbulent flow |work=[[The Hindu]]|author=Sangeetha Devi Dundoo|date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> Vivek Ramz of ''[[in.com|In]]'' noted, "Kadal is a tiring watch and recommended only for die-hard Mani Ratnam fans."<ref name=in>{{cite web |url=http://www.in.com/news/entertainment/kadal-is-a-tiring-watch-50178282-in-1.html |title=Kadal is a tiring watch |publisher=[[in.com]]|author=Vivek Ramz|date=2 February 2013 |accessdate=3 February 2013}}</ref>

==Box office==
The film began receding occupancy post 20 days of its release and was declared as flop<ref name="verd">{{cite web|url=http://truthdive.com/2013/03/03/lingusamys-wonderful-gesture-to-mani-ratnam-seeks-no-compensation-for-kadal-losses.html|title=Lingusamy's wonderful gesture to Mani Ratnam, seeks no compensation for Kadal losses|publisher=TruthDive|date=3 March 2013|accessdate=4 March 2013}}</ref> by Box Office India.

===Domestic===
The film had an average opening in [[Chennai]]. During the weekend of release, the number of shows in Chennai were 603 where as the average theatre occupancy was 70% and the filmed grossed {{INRConvert|16.7|m}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/kadal/kadal-box-office-feb-03.html|title=CHENNAI BOX OFFICE|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=15 February 2013}}</ref> However, certain section of media reported incorrect box office collection leading to contradiction to the actual verdicts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tamil.oneindia.in/movies/news/2013/02/a-mega-lie-on-kadali-box-office-collection-170589.html|title=<U+0B95><U+0B9F><U+0BB2><U+0BCD> <U+0BA4><U+0BC6><U+0BB2><U+0BC1><U+0B99><U+0BCD><U+0B95><U+0BBF><U+0BB2><U+0BCD> <U+0BB0><U+0BC2> 98 <U+0B95><U+0BCB><U+0B9F><U+0BBF> <U+0B95><U+0BC1><U+0BB5><U+0BBF><U+0BA4><U+0BCD><U+0BA4><U+0BC1><U+0BB5><U+0BBF><U+0B9F><U+0BCD><U+0B9F><U+0BA4><U+0BBE><U+0BAE><U+0BCD>... <U+2013> <U+0B92><U+0BB0><U+0BC1> <U+0B9A><U+0BC2><U+0BAA><U+0BCD><U+0BAA><U+0BB0><U+0BCD> <U+0B95><U+0BAA><U+0BCD><U+0B9A><U+0BBE>!!|publisher=OneIndia Entertainment|accessdate=28 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinemalead.com/news-id-boxoffice-kadal-david-disaster-06-02-131291.htm|title=BO REPORT -KADAL AND DAVID :A DISASTER AT THE BOXOFFICE|publisher=CINEMALead|accessdate=28 February 2013}}</ref>

===International===
In the US the film grossed {{INRConvert|03.9|m}} on the opening day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-05/news-interviews/36763970_1_mani-ratnam-tamil-version-christian-community|title=Kadal gets lackluster response in overseas |author= Sashidhar AS|work= [[The Times of India]]| accessdate=15 February 2013}}</ref> In UK and Ireland box office, the film collected <U+00A3>3,189 on 4 screens, with the per screen average working out to <U+00A3>797 summing up to <U+00A3>35,737.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/trade/boxofficeoverseas|title='Special 26' appreciated, 'ABCD <U+2013> Any Body Can Dance' disappoints!|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|author=[[Taran Adarsh]]|accessdate=15 February 2013}}</ref>

==Controversies==
After the release of first theatrical trailer of the film, the osculating scene between the leading debutantes was brought into discussions by media and audience.<ref name=contrvs/> Later, Ratnam clarified that the scene has its own importance, justified in the story line of the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/mani-ratnams-film-in-lip-lock-dispute/1/248013.html |title=Mani Ratnam's film in lip-lock dispute |work=[[India Today]]|date=29 January 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> [[Thulasi Nair]] in 2012 was sixteen years of age and scenes portraying such with minors, this fact added more to the same controversy. However, actress [[Radha (actress)|Radha]], mother of Thulasi, defended stating "As I did Bharathiraja's film ''[[Alaigal Oivathillai]]'', I was aged sixteen. There is a unique style and limitations directors have. They give proper directions to artistes. There is no mistake in doing intimate scenes if it is required for the movie."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tamilstar.com/news-id-celebrities-opine-as-kiss-scenes-happen-in-movies-including-upcoming-kadal-celebrities-opine-as-kiss-scenes-happen-in-movies-including-upcoming-kadal-kadal-movie-23-01-134049.htm |title= Celebrities opine as kiss scenes happen in movies including upcoming 'Kadal' |publisher=TamilStar|date=23 January 2013 |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref> To avoid further repercussions, the osculating scene was chopped off the theatrical prints of the film thereby reducing the running length of the film to 150 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/sri50/status/297326755767779328|title= #Kadal <U+2013> Censor certificate says.... |publisher=Sreedhar Pillai as @Sri50|date=1 February 2013|accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref>

On 5 February 2013, Indian Christian Democratic Party put allegations that ''Kadal'' had objectionable scenes referring to Christianity. They claimed that the film depicted their community in a cloddish manner.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/news/2013/kadal-ban-call-vishwaroopam-103198.html |title=Now, call for ban on Mani Ratnam's Kadal; Will it be another Vishwaroopam?|author=Ramchander|publisher=[[Oneindia.in|One India Entertainment]]|date=4 February 2013 |accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref> The members of the party proposed the deletion those scenes and warned of intensifying their protests. A memorandum in this regard was also submitted by them to police on the same day.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/India-news/Chennai/Now-Mani-Ratnam-s-Kadal-faces-protest-by-Christian-outfit/Article1-1006288.aspx |title=Now Mani Ratnam's 'Kadal' faces protest by Christian outfit|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|location=Chennai|date=4 February 2013 |accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref>

The film distributors suffered financial losses due to performance of the film at the box office and hence, on 9 February 2013, around fifty members, who had taken the theatrical rights of the film for various regions, protested in front of [[Madras Talkies]]' office and demanded the compensation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-10/kadals-distributors-protest-at-madras-talkies-office-kadal-mani-ratnam-10-02-13.html |title=Kadal's distributors protest at Madras Talkies office|publisher=Behindwoods|date=10 February 2013 |accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref> Defending the situation the production house claimed, "Madras Talkies had sold their film 'Kadal' (both Tamil and dubbed Telugu version) to Gemini Industries and Imaging Ltd in March 2012 itself on MG (Minimum Guarantee) basis" They added, "Madras Talkies has had no other dealing with anyone else for the distribution of their film, nor has been party to any contracts Gemini might have entered into in this regard".<ref name=kci>{{cite web |url=http://canindia.com/2013/02/madras-talkies-not-responsible-for-kadal-losses-mani-ratnam/ |title=Madras Talkies not responsible for 'Kadal' losses: Mani Ratnam|publisher=CanIndia|date=10 February 2013 |accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref>

Lingusamy's own production company Thirupathi Brothers had purchased the distribution rights of Mani Ratnam's ''Kadal'' for [[Chennai]], [[Madurai]] and [[Coimbatore]] prior to the release of the movie. To the controversies over film, in a press release dated 2 March 2013, the distributor, on a positive note stated that he would never demand compensation for the losses incurred over acquiring ''Kadal'''s distribution rights. He assured that neither he nor anyone from his office would press Mani Ratnam for compensation of monetary losses incurred over ''Kadal'' at any point of time.<ref name="verd"/>

As per the proceedings of Madras High Court it was learnt that Mannan, one of the distributors for the film and his men issued false statements to let down the reputations of the director. With no basis and intentions to extort money from his clients, the distributor and some miscreants trespassed into Ratnam<U+2019>s office and abused the staff. On March 14, 2013, the judge was passed interim orders on an application arising out of a civil suit from the director and his wife. The suit claimed for a direction to Mannan to pay {{INR}}5 crore towards the damages.<ref name=prd>{{cite web |url=http://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article1500369.ece |title=Mani Ratnam gets HC relief on <U+2018>Kadal<U+2019>|publisher=''[[The New Indian Express]]''|author=Express News Service ([[Chennai]])|date=14 March 2013 |accessdate=17 March 2013}}</ref>

